The paper deals with nonorthogonal multiple access (NOMA) technology, which is primarily used in wireless communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses blind signal classification, which is related to signal processing and machine learning, making cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) possible categories. The joint optimization problem for user scheduling and power allocation involves system-level considerations, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, since the paper deals with wireless communication systems, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category.
